abstract: Caisse de Dépôt et Placement du Québec, Canada’s biggest pension-fund manager, is looking to unload a $800 million private-equity portfolio, Dow Jones reported.
snippet: Caisse de Dépôt et Placement du Québec, Canada’s biggest pension-fund manager, is looking to unload a $800 million private-equity portfolio, Dow Jones reported.
lead_paragraph: Caisse de Dépôt et Placement du Québec, Canada’s biggest pension-fund manager, is looking to unload an $800 million private-equity portfolio, Dow Jones reported, citing people familiar with the transaction.

headline.main: Caisse de Dépôt Said to Shop $800 Million P.E. Fund
